1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
In Pęgów,
there are several
old houses.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Can you guess
which one is the oldest?

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Maybe it is the palace
in the village center?

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
No!

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:19,000
The oldest house
is not grand at all.

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:23,000
It is actually
in very poor condition.

7
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:27,000
It fits its age
very well.

8
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,000
It is over 100 years old

9
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:35,000
and was built
in the 19th century.

10
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Its walls show
how it was built.

11
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:43,000
This is called
"Prussian wall".

12
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:47,000
It is a wooden frame
filled with bricks.

13
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Or maybe it is not
Prussian wall?

14
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Maybe it is
a wattle and daub wall,

15
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,000
filled with clay
and straw instead?

16
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,000
What do you think?

17
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Can you tell
the difference?

18
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:09,000
There are more houses
over 100 years old.

19
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Look at the old shop
made of brick.

20
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:17,000
It used to be
an inn.

21
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Also the villas
near the train station.

22
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:25,000
They show
old village wealth.

23
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Everything was centered here,

24
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:33,000
close to the railway.

25
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:37,000
For a long time,
it was the only good link

26
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
to Wrocław.